00:23:55,950 --> 00:23:57,930
 (Choi Won Ho: Headmaster of Baegyu Painting Institute)  

234
00:23:58,730 --> 00:24:02,520
It is a painting that I drew

235
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:07,400
of the street vendors' cock fight when I was a student at the painting school.

236
00:24:07,450 --> 00:24:08,830
 (Gyeonju Daek : Baegyu Painting Institute's housekeeper) 

237
00:24:08,830 --> 00:24:11,010
Oh, Chun Bok!

238
00:24:11,010 --> 00:24:12,430
 (Kang Chun Bok: Chief Steward of the Baegyu Painting Institute)  
 Yes, sir?

239
00:24:12,430 --> 00:24:15,920
Watch over the kids while they paint.

240
00:24:16,910 --> 00:24:18,870
Headmaster?

241
00:24:18,870 --> 00:24:21,300
Headmaster, where are you going?

242
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:23,130
Headmaster?

243
00:24:26,620 --> 00:24:29,950
All right. Elements to learn from this painting is...

244
00:24:29,950 --> 00:24:33,160
So what are we doing here?

245
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:35,710
You would not understand even if I told you.

246
00:24:35,710 --> 00:24:37,630
Come now, tell me.

247
00:24:37,630 --> 00:24:40,650
Do you expect me to answer you for free?

248
00:24:40,650 --> 00:24:42,320
Do you expect me to pay you?

249
00:24:42,320 --> 00:24:45,730
Nothing in this world is free.

250
00:24:45,730 --> 00:24:47,290
Never mind, then!

251
00:24:47,290 --> 00:24:50,160
I'm not curious in the slightest.

252
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:51,890
This moment of them flying into the air...

253
00:24:51,890 --> 00:24:53,960
- All right.
- sets an anticipatory atmosphere...

254
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:56,890
Close your eyes.

255
00:24:56,890 --> 00:24:59,040
What if I don't?

256
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:07,870
If you close your eyes like this, you can hear sounds.

257
00:25:23,010 --> 00:25:24,860
Do you hear them?

258
00:25:29,030 --> 00:25:33,710
This is the sound of brushes against the paper.

259
00:25:33,710 --> 00:25:35,810
Gliding...

260
00:25:35,810 --> 00:25:38,060
and sliding...

261
00:25:38,870 --> 00:25:41,110
You are a fast learner.

262
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:47,800
As you listen to the sounds, you begin to imagine the painting.

263
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:53,020
And as you imagine the painting, you feel content.

264
00:25:53,020 --> 00:25:57,300
Because I see the world through sound.

265
00:26:06,700 --> 00:26:08,800
Here... 
  (Gyeonju Daek: the house owner and housekeeper)  

266
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:11,450
Gyeonju Daek*... 
 (= "woman from Gyeonju". But it's used instead of her name) 

267
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:17,190
Headmaster...  (Gyeonju Daek: thehouse owner)  

268
00:26:17,190 --> 00:26:18,880
Gyeonju Daek.

269
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:20,790
Ajeossi!

270
00:26:21,470 --> 00:26:23,040
Ch-Cheon Gi!

271
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:25,530
We have run out of vermilion dye at home.

272
00:26:25,530 --> 00:26:27,520
Could I take your leftovers?

273
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:29,750
Sure, go ahead.

274
00:26:29,750 --> 00:26:32,440
All right. Thank you, sir.

275
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:47,960
- Ajeossi?
 - What? What is it? What?

276
00:26:49,260 --> 00:26:52,330
Where did Gyeonju Daek go?

277
00:26:52,330 --> 00:26:57,600
She said she would give me something, but I do not think she's in the kitchen.

278
00:26:57,600 --> 00:26:59,710
The bundle in the shed. The bundle in the shed.

279
00:26:59,710 --> 00:27:01,970
The bundle in the shed.

280
00:27:01,970 --> 00:27:04,480
She says there is a bundle in the shed.

281
00:27:04,480 --> 00:27:05,800
That's right!

282
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:08,570
The bundle in the shed! What a bright young man.

283
00:27:08,570 --> 00:27:11,070
- Why don't you go look for it with her?
 - Yes, sir.

284
00:27:11,070 --> 00:27:12,920
Let's go, Cheon Gi.

285
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:27,500
Gyeonju Daek...

286
00:27:27,500 --> 00:27:29,640
Headmaster, we've finished—

287
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:35,210
- I quit! I say, I quit!
 - Headmaster, please!

288
00:27:35,210 --> 00:27:38,000
I quit! Is that what you want? I quit!

289
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:40,920
You dim-witted fool!

290
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:44,170
It was a mistake taking you in!

291
00:27:44,770 --> 00:27:46,860
I wonder...

292
00:27:46,860 --> 00:27:50,770
how did you know the bundle was in the shed?

293
00:27:50,770 --> 00:27:54,380
That's... that is...

294
00:27:54,380 --> 00:27:57,110
Cheon Gi, there you are.

295
00:27:57,110 --> 00:28:02,190
Gyeonju Daek! I thought you had gone somewhere.

296
00:28:02,190 --> 00:28:04,980
No, that's not it.

297
00:28:04,980 --> 00:28:07,100
Cheon Gi, hold on.

298
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:10,130
What is wrong with your sleeve?

299
00:28:10,130 --> 00:28:12,610
One moment. I will sew it back together in no time.

300
00:28:12,610 --> 00:28:14,740
Wait here for a moment.

301
00:28:17,100 --> 00:28:20,740
Did you pretend not to see it when you saw the hole?

302
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:26,200
I always get holes in my clothes, so I thought you were the same.

303
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:29,900
Do you also not have a mother?

304
00:28:29,900 --> 00:28:31,460
I do.

305
00:28:31,460 --> 00:28:35,480
Why? You don't have a mother?

306
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:40,880
She died the day I was born.

307
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:56,280
What are you drawing all of a sudden?

308
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:02,960
A star.

309
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:08,070
This looks more like a full moon than a star.

310
00:29:08,070 --> 00:29:12,240
This is a star to me.

311
00:29:25,380 --> 00:29:26,770
What are you doing?

312
00:29:26,770 --> 00:29:29,160
I shall draw with you.

313
00:29:52,490 --> 00:29:54,820
This is a star?

314
00:29:54,820 --> 00:29:58,140
Yes. The Big Dipper.

315
00:29:58,140 --> 00:30:00,150
I see.

316
00:30:00,150 --> 00:30:03,100
The Big Dipper...

317
00:30:06,570 --> 00:30:08,170
Are you hungry?

318
00:30:08,170 --> 00:30:10,690
N... no!

319
00:30:12,800 --> 00:30:15,050
Follow me!

320
00:30:18,180 --> 00:30:19,560
No.

321
00:30:27,910 --> 00:30:29,680
Children.

322
00:30:31,050 --> 00:30:32,700
Come here.

323
00:30:32,700 --> 00:30:34,910
- Us?
 - Yes!

324
00:30:34,910 --> 00:30:37,300
You two, come here.

325
00:30:40,580 --> 00:30:42,420
Hold on, hold on.

326
00:30:43,900 --> 00:30:48,500
Here. You will need this tomorrow.

327
00:30:48,500 --> 00:30:50,910
No, that is all right.

328
00:30:50,910 --> 00:30:53,150
I can't take this from you.

329
00:30:53,150 --> 00:30:55,390
Take what?

330
00:30:57,020 --> 00:30:58,480
Huh?

331
00:31:00,290 --> 00:31:02,290
What's wrong?

332
00:31:02,290 --> 00:31:03,840
What is it?

333
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:05,430
It is nothing...

334
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:08,300
I must have imagined it.

335
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:14,750
Let's go.

336
00:31:17,010 --> 00:31:20,040
Be sure to hold your hands tightly together.

337
00:31:20,040 --> 00:31:23,080
 So they have finally met. 

338
00:31:24,340 --> 00:31:25,500
 (Seongjucheong:  Shamanist Bureau)  

339
00:31:25,500 --> 00:31:28,900
But what brings you to Gwanyang?

340
00:31:28,950 --> 00:31:32,370
What a cruel joke of fate.

341
00:31:32,370 --> 00:31:37,840
My son is to be Seokcheokdongja for the rain ritual this year.

342
00:31:37,840 --> 00:31:41,660
Ha Ram is born with the power of water.

343
00:31:41,660 --> 00:31:44,950
So he is going to the palace?

344
00:31:44,950 --> 00:31:46,980
That cannot be.

345
00:31:51,170 --> 00:31:52,310
What?

346
00:31:52,310 --> 00:31:55,210
You have found a boy suitable for the Seokcheok Rain Ritual?

347
00:31:55,210 --> 00:31:56,510
Yes, Your Majesty.

348
00:31:56,510 --> 00:31:59,190
The Shamanistic Bureau has him under its protection.

349
00:31:59,190 --> 00:32:00,230
Who is it?

350
00:32:00,230 --> 00:32:04,010
He is the son of Ha Seong Jin, who once carried out rituals as head of the Taoist Bureau.

351
00:32:04,010 --> 00:32:06,940
The boy is blessed by the water god.

352
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:10,880
Is the man who sealed Ma Wang nine years ago still alive?

353
00:32:10,880 --> 00:32:16,660
Yes, Your Majesty.  It seems he escaped and stayed hidden in Yangju.

354
00:32:19,430 --> 00:32:21,560
That is a relief.

355
00:32:23,090 --> 00:32:28,700
But it pains me that we must sacrifice his son.

356
00:32:28,700 --> 00:32:34,280
You must swallow your pain and make a decision for the starving people.

357
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:38,800
Are you suggesting a human sacrifice?

358
00:32:41,030 --> 00:32:43,140
Your Majesty, a hundred years ago,

359
00:32:43,140 --> 00:32:46,980
a human sacrifice relieved heaven's anger and brought down rain.

360
00:32:46,980 --> 00:32:50,540
How dare you speak such words in front of His Majesty!

361
00:32:50,540 --> 00:32:52,620
We are a country that follows Confucius' and Mencius' teachings.

362
00:32:52,620 --> 00:32:54,690
We cannot carry out something so preposterous!

363
00:32:54,690 --> 00:32:58,920
Your Excellencies, have you forgotten about the incident nine years ago?

364
00:32:58,920 --> 00:33:01,220
The drought and famine have continued for years.

365
00:33:01,220 --> 00:33:05,470
Human sacrifice is the only way to undo Ma Wang's curse.

366
00:33:05,470 --> 00:33:09,980
In whose presence are you, a mere shaman, freely wagging your tongue?

367
00:33:09,980 --> 00:33:11,760
What are your thoughts on this?

368
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:15,120
The will of the heavens will not change through human deceptions.

369
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:18,970
How could the gods allow human sacrifice?

370
00:33:18,970 --> 00:33:21,490
I am of the same mind.

371
00:33:22,660 --> 00:33:25,580
The rain ritual will be carried out in a dignified manner this year.

372
00:33:25,580 --> 00:33:27,690
We shall not sacrifice any life.

373
00:33:27,690 --> 00:33:28,940
Is that understood?

374
00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:31,640
 Yes, Your Majesty. 

375
00:33:31,640 --> 00:33:35,840
 Only a human sacrifice will bring rain, Your Majesty. 

376
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:40,130
 You may all disagree with me, but I must do it. 

377
00:33:40,130 --> 00:33:42,880
 The royal shaman will do it. 

378
00:33:59,340 --> 00:34:00,880
Hey!

379
00:34:00,880 --> 00:34:04,540
What are you doing?  This is theft!

380
00:34:27,100 --> 00:34:29,090
Hey, wait, wait.

381
00:34:29,090 --> 00:34:30,910
There is someone here.

382
00:34:30,910 --> 00:34:33,500
Do you not hear her snoring?

383
00:34:35,050 --> 00:34:36,590
You're a psychic.

384
00:34:36,590 --> 00:34:38,560
See this stick?

385
00:34:38,560 --> 00:34:40,560
I do.

386
00:34:40,560 --> 00:34:42,150
Use it to steal them.

387
00:34:44,010 --> 00:34:47,100
Why don't we just tell Father we are hungry?

388
00:34:47,150 --> 00:34:51,150
Do you wish to trouble an elder during this time of famine?

389
00:34:52,010 --> 00:34:53,900
All right.

390
00:35:14,820 --> 00:35:16,470
Be quiet!

391
00:35:16,470 --> 00:35:21,920
Everyone in the village knows about Anseong Daek* of the peach tree field. 
 (lit: Woman from Anseong) 

392
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:22,930
Why?

393
00:35:22,950 --> 00:35:27,890
Because her fiery temper will make even grown men tremble with fear.

394
00:35:27,890 --> 00:35:29,500
Then she's a scary person!

395
00:35:29,500 --> 00:35:33,490
If we get caught, we won't be able to walk out on our own.

396
00:35:33,490 --> 00:35:34,750
What?

397
00:35:34,750 --> 00:35:38,670
I won't do it then! I'm coming down.

398
00:35:40,450 --> 00:35:42,950
I want to eat a peach.

399
00:35:43,630 --> 00:35:47,690
I can't even pick a peach because I can't see.

400
00:35:49,810 --> 00:35:51,730
All right, fine.

401
00:36:39,440 --> 00:36:41,790
Are you all right?

402
00:36:44,150 --> 00:36:46,220
Who's there?

403
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:52,010
- You scoundrels! 
 - Hey, run!

404
00:36:52,010 --> 00:36:53,600
Oh, all right.

405
00:37:05,160 --> 00:37:07,130
She's coming! Hurry!

406
00:37:13,350 --> 00:37:15,130
Are you all right? Let's go!

407
00:37:15,130 --> 00:37:18,580
You brats! Don't you try that again!

408
00:37:29,170 --> 00:37:30,440
This is all your fault.

409
00:37:30,450 --> 00:37:35,550
If it weren't for you, we wouldn't have been chased by someone who's scary as a ghost.

410
00:37:36,930 --> 00:37:38,750
Where are you going?

411
00:37:39,970 --> 00:37:41,790
I hate you.

412
00:37:44,540 --> 00:37:47,460
I never said I wanted to steal someone else's peaches.

413
00:37:47,460 --> 00:37:49,670
You are just like everyone else.

414
00:37:49,670 --> 00:37:52,600
Because I can't see...

415
00:37:52,600 --> 00:37:55,740
and because my father isn't mentally well,

416
00:37:57,340 --> 00:38:00,700
and because my mother died when I was born...

417
00:38:00,700 --> 00:38:03,630
I have no friends.

418
00:38:03,630 --> 00:38:07,230
Everyone points fingers at me for no reason.

419
00:38:07,230 --> 00:38:10,050
They say I am a cursed child.

420
00:38:10,050 --> 00:38:15,180
I only wanted to eat a peach with you.

421
00:38:19,530 --> 00:38:21,640
I'm sorry.

422
00:38:29,180 --> 00:38:31,460
But...

423
00:38:31,460 --> 00:38:34,810
the fact that your mother died giving birth to you,

424
00:38:34,810 --> 00:38:38,600
that you were born blind,

425
00:38:38,600 --> 00:38:42,990
that your father isn't mentally well...

426
00:38:42,990 --> 00:38:44,630
none of those is your fault.

427
00:38:44,630 --> 00:38:46,960
- So why...
- Why what?

428
00:38:46,960 --> 00:38:48,580
What?

429
00:38:48,580 --> 00:38:50,540
What do you know?

430
00:38:52,180 --> 00:38:53,850
You're right.

431
00:38:53,850 --> 00:38:58,250
I don't know anything, but you can't help it.

432
00:38:59,080 --> 00:39:03,950
Everything that has happened to you is not within the human will.

433
00:39:03,950 --> 00:39:07,040
It isn't your fault!

434
00:39:08,950 --> 00:39:15,050
So don't blame yourself for things that you cannot control.

435
00:39:23,920 --> 00:39:28,350
I'm even hungrier now from running so much.

436
00:39:28,350 --> 00:39:32,360
This definitely is your fault.

437
00:39:37,070 --> 00:39:38,640
Here.

438
00:39:46,510 --> 00:39:48,240
It's still not ripe.

439
00:39:48,240 --> 00:39:51,370
It's sweet. Tastes delicious.

440
00:40:01,050 --> 00:40:02,950
What is that?

441
00:40:21,130 --> 00:40:23,570
It should feel better now.

442
00:40:31,290 --> 00:40:33,120
Where did the bundle go?

443
00:40:33,120 --> 00:40:34,500
Oh, right!

444
00:40:34,500 --> 00:40:36,430
Gyeonju Daek's bundle!

445
00:40:36,430 --> 00:40:39,380
I must have lost it while we were running away.

446
00:40:39,380 --> 00:40:41,390
Here it is.

447
00:40:41,390 --> 00:40:42,950
Really?

448
00:40:44,660 --> 00:40:45,960
Thank goodness.

449
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:47,940
Why would you jest about such a thing?

450
00:40:47,950 --> 00:40:50,550
You really startled me.

451
00:40:51,560 --> 00:40:53,340
You are so mean.

452
00:40:53,340 --> 00:40:55,750
I can't even jest.

453
00:40:57,320 --> 00:41:02,040
There are countless stars in the sky tonight.

454
00:41:02,790 --> 00:41:05,900
Look, there's the Big Dipper.

455
00:41:05,900 --> 00:41:07,580
Is there?

456
00:41:09,610 --> 00:41:11,300
Wow...

457
00:41:16,250 --> 00:41:20,150
- Oh, right.
- Oh, right what?

458
00:41:20,820 --> 00:41:23,530
Do you feel guilty about seeing the stars by yourself?

459
00:41:23,530 --> 00:41:25,560
I'm sorry.

460
00:41:25,560 --> 00:41:28,160
It was insensitive of me.

461
00:41:30,820 --> 00:41:33,450
How many stars are there?

462
00:41:35,130 --> 00:41:37,350
Around a hundred million?

463
00:41:37,350 --> 00:41:41,200
How much is a hundred million?

464
00:41:41,200 --> 00:41:45,440
A lot. Quite a lot.

465
00:41:54,110 --> 00:41:56,700
Get off now. We're here.

466
00:41:59,300 --> 00:42:01,200
Wait.

467
00:42:05,340 --> 00:42:08,590
Here. You should take this.

468
00:42:08,590 --> 00:42:10,740
That's all right.

469
00:42:10,740 --> 00:42:14,810
I'll come to fetch it after the rain ritual.

470
00:42:14,810 --> 00:42:18,450
Isn't this precious to you?

471
00:42:18,470 --> 00:42:19,800
This?

472
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:21,260
It is nothing.

473
00:42:21,260 --> 00:42:26,660
It is just the one and only handkerchief that my mother gave me.

474
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:31,230
Are you telling the truth?

475
00:42:32,590 --> 00:42:35,500
All right. Come back tomorrow.

476
00:42:35,500 --> 00:42:37,390
I'll be waiting for you.

477
00:42:38,140 --> 00:42:39,670
All right.

478
00:42:41,910 --> 00:42:48,010
Tomorrow, I'll go back to Anseong Daek's peach tree field and steal more peaches for you.

479
00:42:49,970 --> 00:42:52,430
Give me your hand.

480
00:42:52,430 --> 00:42:54,030
My hand?

481
00:43:50,870 --> 00:43:53,690
Here.

482
00:43:56,520 --> 00:43:58,650
Take this.

483
00:44:02,010 --> 00:44:06,530
You will go pick peaches with me tomorrow, won't you?

484
00:44:06,530 --> 00:44:09,070
Sure. Of course!

485
00:44:10,750 --> 00:44:13,250
Fine. That's a promise.

486
00:44:14,190 --> 00:44:15,820
All right.

487
00:44:17,480 --> 00:44:19,040
Let's go.

488
00:44:56,760 --> 00:45:01,250
His Majesty, the King!

489
00:45:12,020 --> 00:45:14,730
You must be Ha Ram.

490
00:45:16,250 --> 00:45:21,410
I lack virtue and must depend on a young boy like you.

491
00:45:22,270 --> 00:45:26,000
I am hugely indebted to your family.

492
00:45:26,760 --> 00:45:28,960
Please do not mention it, Your Majesty.

493
00:45:34,300 --> 00:45:36,980
The eyes are the most important thing in a painting.

494
00:45:36,980 --> 00:45:39,310
The soul must be clear!

495
00:45:39,310 --> 00:45:40,770
Goodness!

496
00:45:40,770 --> 00:45:42,310
Oh, my!

497
00:45:42,310 --> 00:45:45,570
What insolence!

498
00:45:59,740 --> 00:46:03,660
Have mercy!

499
00:46:03,670 --> 00:46:06,230
Have mercy, please!

500
00:46:09,550 --> 00:46:14,590
 Father, I hear they got really good medicine this time. 

501
00:46:14,590 --> 00:46:16,480
 Hold on... 

502
00:46:16,480 --> 00:46:19,010
 Hold on just a little bit longer. 

503
00:46:28,090 --> 00:46:31,760
His Highness, the Crown Prince!

504
00:46:41,200 --> 00:46:44,480
 (Crown Prince Yi Kang: Seongjo's eldest son)  
 Hu, it's been too long.

505
00:46:44,480 --> 00:46:46,960
Why have you not visited me all this time?

506
00:46:46,960 --> 00:46:50,550
 (Grand Prince Juhyang, Yi Hu: Seongjo's second son) 
 Your Highness, you must speak with formality.

507
00:46:50,550 --> 00:46:53,470
- There are people watching.
 - No matter.

508
00:46:53,470 --> 00:46:56,380
We are brothers of the same mother.

509
00:46:56,380 --> 00:47:00,110
It is a delight to see my brothers here.

510
00:47:00,110 --> 00:47:06,530
Your Highness, our country is suffering from a lengthy drought and famine.

511
00:47:06,530 --> 00:47:08,510
Before the personal joy of seeing each other,

512
00:47:08,510 --> 00:47:12,690
I pray you do not forget the significance of today's rain ritual.

513
00:47:12,690 --> 00:47:19,190
Hu, I will not forget your loyal counsel when I ascend the throne.

514
00:47:19,190 --> 00:47:22,290
Yes, Your Highness.

515
00:47:22,290 --> 00:47:23,700
Come now, Hyeong-nim*. 
  (=elder brother) 

516
00:47:23,700 --> 00:47:26,170
Why are you acting so formally?

517
00:47:26,170 --> 00:47:30,930
Yul, when I said that to His Highness, I knew full well what it meant.

518
00:47:30,930 --> 00:47:33,180
That is enough, Yul.

519
00:47:33,180 --> 00:47:35,770
Hu speaks for my own good.

520
00:47:35,770 --> 00:47:37,120
 (Grand Prince Yangmyeong, Yi Yul: Seongjo's third son) 

521
00:47:37,120 --> 00:47:39,410
I understand, Your Highness.

